==English==

===Pronunciation===
*(''adjective''): kĕlʹtĭk, /ˈkeltɪk/, /<tt>"keltIk</tt>/
*(''proper noun''): sĕlʹtĭk, /ˈseltɪk/, /<tt>"seltIk</tt>/

===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[Κελτικός]]''' (''Keltikos'') "of or related to the [[Celts]]".

[[Category:English heteronyms|celtic]]

===Noun===
'''Celtic'''

# A branch of the [[Indo-European]] languages that was spread widely over western and central Europe in the pre-Christian era.


===Adjective===
'''Celtic'''

# Of the [[Celts]]; Of the style of the [[Celts]]

